<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-02-12"><hi rend="italic">February 12,
                                    1901</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Loomis reports that the Venezuelan Government protests most strongly
                            against the presence of the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Scorpion</hi> in
                            the Orinoco River without having asked permission to enter, declaring
                            such presence to be in violation of Venezuelan as well as of
                            international laws.</p>
                        <p>Instructions as to proper reply requested.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>